Commentary Text: Siraj to Karthik, out Caught by Srikar Bharat!! Bharat is celebrating a catch. It's been referred upstairs to see if it's carried. Seems that it's gone straight into the gloves on the first replay. The third umpire wants to look at it from side-on. Taking plenty of time. The zoomed-up replay is very blurry. But before the third umpire even makes the decision, Karthik walks off. He's convinced he's out. And sure enough OUT flashes on the big screen. Again Siraj beats a batter for pace, with the ball skidding through from back of a length. Karthik is late on the cut and toe-edges it. The ball dies to the keeper, but he seems to grab it clean. Karthik c Srikar Bharat b Siraj 10(12) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Chahal to Tripathi, out Lbw!! Pad first, definitely pad first. Umpire says not out, and Kohli has taken the review. It's a googly that turns in from a length on middle, hits the knee-roll, then onto the inside edge. RCB players roar as they see the first replay. And it's three reds as the ball is crashing into the top of leg stump. The third time that a decision from umpire Virender Sharma has been overturned tonight. Tripathi lbw b Chahal 6(5) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, out Caught by de Villiers!! 114.3kph. Slower cutter. And it brings him #31. He pitches it up, and Gill - poor foxed Gill - dances down, makes room, tries tonking it downtown. Ends up slicing it with his bottom-hand off the handle too, and ends up with only height, with distance equalling mid-on. So Harshal's one wicket behind Bravo's all-time count of 32, and he's found his first ever wicket in the powerplay this season. Shubman Gill c de Villiers b Harshal Patel 29(18) [4s-4]
